Hola David,

Gracias por la aclaracion.  Confio en que esta vez si se obtiene lo que
buscas:

R> set.seed(123)
R> A <- matrix(rpois(20, 4), ncol = 4)
R> B <- matrix(rpois(274*3, 4), ncol = 3)
R> A
#     [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
#[1,]    3    1    8    7
#[2,]    6    4    4    3
#[3,]    3    7    5    1
#[4,]    6    4    4    3
#[5,]    7    4    2    8

R> # el resultado es una matriz de orden 5x3
R> sapply(1:ncol(B), function(.col) sapply(A[, .col + 1], function(x)
sum(B[, .col] > x)))
#        [,1] [,2] [,3]
#[1,]  256    9   13
#[2,]   98  102  157
#[3,]   14   59  244
#[4,]   98  102  157
#[5,]   98  206    6

Ahora hagamos los calculos para los elementos de A:

R> sum(B[,1] > A[1,2])
# [1] 256
R> sum(B[,1] > A[2,2])
# [1] 98
R> sum(B[,1] > A[3,2])
# [1] 14
R> sum(B[,1] > A[4,2])
# [1] 98
R> sum(B[,1] > A[5,2])
# [1] 98
R> sum(B[,2] > A[1,3])
# [1] 9
R> sum(B[,2] > A[2,3])
# [1] 102
R> sum(B[,2] > A[3,3])
# [1] 59
R> sum(B[,2] > A[4,3])
# [1] 102
R> sum(B[,2] > A[5,3])
# [1] 206
R> sum(B[,3] > A[1,4])
# [1] 13
R> sum(B[,3] > A[2,4])
# [1] 157
R> sum(B[,3] > A[3,4])
# [1] 244
R> sum(B[,3] > A[4,4])
# [1] 157
R> sum(B[,3] > A[5,4])
# [1] 6

Saludos,
Jorge.-



